  "commentary": "With SPX at 7005 sitting directly on the massive 19.97B gamma wall at 7000, dealers are aggressively selling into this strength to hedge their long gamma positions, creating immediate resistance. The PIN regime and thick positive gamma walls from 7000-7100 should cap upside momentum and drive mean reversion back toward the 6860 flip level. Watch for rejection at 7025 (11.7B wall) if price pushes higher, while any break below 7000 should accelerate selling pressure toward the negative gamma zone at 6800.\n\nBottom line: expect the market to get rejected around current levels and pull back.",
